subSubSection.paragraph:
Shell (
Fig. 6B
):

Shell medium (width ≤ 35.0 mm, height ≤ 
24.5 mm
), conic to slightly depressed conic, thickened and dull, dextral and narrow perforate. Whorls six to eight, increasing regularly; suture wide and little depressed. Shell colour brownish to yellowish; below periphery with paler colour than upper periphery. Spire convex; apex acute; embryonic shell small and with fine radial ridges. Shell surface coarse, with nodule lines arranged on fine radial ridges; below periphery with nearly smooth surface around umbilicus. Last whorl angular, with weak peripheral keel. Aperture ovate; parietal callus transparent; lip simple, slightly thickened and little expanded near columellar area. Columella slightly dilated. Umbilicus perforate, narrow and deep.
